President Obama has announced his intent to nominate two individuals to key administration posts. Robert Stephen Ford is nominated for Ambassador to the Syrian Arab Republic, Department of State. He has a long career in the Foreign Service and has served in various posts since 1985. Jonathan Andrew Hatfield is nominated for Inspector General, Corporation for National and Community Service. He has been with the Federal Election Commission Office of Inspector General since 1994 and has received several awards for his accomplishments. Hatfield holds a B.B.A. in Accounting and is a Certified Public Accountant.